Question For a given positive integer N, you need to calculate S=1!+2!+3!+â€¦+N!.
Input The input gives a positive integer N not exceeding 10 in a row.
Output Print the value of S in one line.
Sample Input 3 Sample Output 9 Answer (C) Loop to find factorial.
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; int get(int num) { int sum = 1; for (int i = 1; i &lt;= num; i++) sum *= i; return sum; } int main() { int i = 0; scanf(&#34;%d&#34;, &amp;i); int sum = 0; for (int j = 1; j &lt;= i; j++) sum += get(j); printf(&#34;%d\n&#34;, sum); }
